 Femi Folaranmi, Yenagoa  Three female students of the Bayelsa State College of Health Technology, Otuogidi, Ogbia Local Government Area of Bayelsa State have been abducted by armed men in Bayelsa State. The three students in their final year were on their way to school when suspected kidnapped ambushed them and whisked them an unknown destination. A community source said the three students were kidnapped close to the check point where two policemen were killed few days to the last governorship election. “The girls were walking to their hostel from school when some men appeared from the bush and accosted them. They seized them and took them to unknown place. They must have been armed. They took the girls across the River.”  Investigations revealed that the kidnapped of the students has caused apprehension in the School as many of the students are demanding answers from the school authority. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Mr Asinim Butswat, when contacted said he was touch with the Divisional Police Officer for Ogbia Local Government Area to get details of the incident from him.